4.30	Mandarava	Mandarava	Mandarava is, along with Yeshe Tsogyal, one of the two principal consorts of Padmasambhava and is considered a female guru-deity. Mandarava, born a princess in Mandi, Himachel Pradesh, India in the 8th Century CE, renounced her royal birthright in order to practice the Dharma, and became a fully realized spiritual adept and great teacher.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Flower_I_IMG_3974.jpg/220px-Flower_I_IMG_3974.jpg
